<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="585" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,258,931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,726,751]" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Morrison, 1973" authorityName="Morrison" authorityYear="1973" box="[613,922,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcatus">
<emphasis box="[613,739,727,751]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">H. furcatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[747,922,726,751]" pageId="5" pageNumber="585" refId="ref4219" refString="SMorrison, W. P. (1973) A revision of the Hecalinae (HomoPtera) of the Oriental Region. Pacific Insects, 15 (3 &amp; 4), 379 - 438." type="journal article">Morrison, 1973</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the shiny pale yellow colour of adult with two lines on the anterior margin of the crown; the aedeagus with a pair of lateral flares near the apex and the shaft keeled ventrally with many teeth and broadened medially. It also differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Dash &amp; Viraktamath, 1997" authorityName="Dash &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidus">
<emphasis box="[1213,1330,798,822]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">H. bifidus</emphasis>
Dash &amp; Viraktamath, 
<quantity box="[304,360,835,859]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.07238" pageId="5" pageNumber="585" unit="in" value="1997.0">1997</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in its colour pattern and two lines on anterior margin of crown; and the aedeagus with a pair of lateral flares and shaft ventrally keeled with many teeth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
